cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about syntactic constituency parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a sequence-to-sequence model, which is a popular deep learning architecture, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper uses attention mechanisms, which are a common technique in NLP, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. The paper also mentions that their parser is fast, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could be a relevant category. Finally, the paper uses a synthetic corpus to train their model, which could be considered a form of data augmentation, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible category.
